# n6-architecture /.own — L1 unified governance DSL (23 rules)
# Project-local SSOT: declarative rules + cron loop + forward-chain + drift checks.
# Parallel to L0 (hexa-lang /.raw) with independent id namespace.
# Grammar: hexa-lang self/raw_loader.hexa (same syntax as .raw / .loop / .chain).
# Populated from .md mandates + migrated .loop + migrated loop-rules.json.
# raw#20 own-monotonic — exclude .raw duplicates.
#
# Unified rule fields (all optional except slug / status / since / why):
#   -- declarative --
#   slug <id>           stable identifier (external ref: own:<slug>)
#   decl <paths...>     declaration / enforcement files
#   scope <text>        rule coverage
#   why <text>          motivation
#   note <text>         supplementary
#   deps <refs...>      own:<slug> / raw:<slug>
#   -- verification (absorbs .loop) --
#   verify <shell-cmd>  exit 0 = PASS, non-zero = FAIL
#   cron <sched>        on-commit|pre-push|hourly|daily|weekly|manual
#   on_fail <action>    block|warn|log
#   label <text>        runner display
#   -- drift (absorbs loop-rules.json) --
#   drift_doc <file>        doc file
#   drift_pattern <regex>   current-value extractor
#   drift_actual <cmd>      ground-truth shell cmd
#   -- forward-chain (raw#0 step.<id>.<prop>) --
#   step.<id>.cmd <cmd>     step shell
#   step.<id>.timeout <s>   step timeout
#   mode strict|loose       prev-marker policy
#   ttl <sec>               marker TTL
#
# Runner: hexa tool/own_runner.hexa <subcommand>
#   list | verify <slug> | verify-all | drift <slug> | drift-all
#   cron <schedule> | schema
#
# Legacy files shadowed (kept for backward-compat readers, .own is authoritative):
#   .loop             -> own#18, own#19 (migrated 2026-04-21)
#   loop-rules.json   -> own#20, own#21 (migrated 2026-04-21)

own 1 live "doc-english-required — English documentation required (HARD)"
  slug doc-english-required
  decl .md documents under (domains/, engine/, theory/, theory/*, reports/, experiments/, papers/, bridge/, n6shared/, proposals/, each chip-* domain) + CONTRIBUTING.md + source comments + commit messages tool/own_doc_lint.py tool/own1_legacy_allowlist.json
  scope HARD block — project-wide English-only for .md files; allowlist is shrink-only. Covers domains/, theory/, reports/, experiments/, papers/, bridge/, n6shared/, proposals/ + CONTRIBUTING.md (1059 legacy files allowlisted via tool/own1_legacy_allowlist.json as of 2026-04-24). Root README.md governed by own#17 separately.
  status live
  since 2026-04-21
  why n6-architecture language policy — documents, comments, commits must be English primary. arXiv compatibility + international contribution priority. Promoted from SOFT log to HARD block on 2026-04-24 via user 'hard go' directive; scope re-extended project-wide on 2026-04-24 via user 'hard!!! 모두 english only' directive. Allowlist entries may be removed upon translation but never added. Any new .md must be English. Legacy CJK .md files grandfathered and frozen in OWN1_LEGACY_ALLOWLIST sidecar.
  note hexa-lang /.raw has no equivalent — project-specific. Legacy allowlist is a FROZEN, shrink-only grandfather list; no new grandfather entries. New CJK .md files under decl scope fail the HARD check.
  verify python3 tool/own_doc_lint.py --rule 1
  cron on-commit
  on_fail block
  label own#1 doc-english HARD gate

