  drift_pattern tests:\s+\d+
  drift_actual python3 tool/own_nexus6_tests_drift.py
  cron daily
  on_fail warn
  label NEXUS-6 test count

own 22 live "proposal-naming — proposal filename category convention (HARD)"
  slug proposal-naming
  decl proposals/ tool/proposal_lint.py
  scope HARD block — proposals/*.md filenames must match category-derived naming pattern. category=identity → kebab-case, no date suffix. category=operational → snake_case + _YYYY_MM_DD. category=phased → kebab-case + -YYYY-MM-DD. Mismatch between declared (frontmatter `category:`) and inferred-from-filename pattern blocks commit.
  status live
  since 2026-04-25
  why filename predicts proposal lifecycle (identity = durable strategic doc, operational = dated audit/op artifact, phased = dated rollout phase). Convention drift erodes the predictive signal and causes proposal repo navigation friction. Promoted to HARD via user '강제' directive on 2026-04-25.
  verify python3 tool/proposal_lint.py --rule 1
  cron on-commit
  on_fail block
  label own#22 proposal-naming HARD gate

