own 29 live "readme-friendly-toolkit-required — README friendly toolkit table generalized across domain sections (HARD)"
  slug readme-friendly-toolkit-required
  decl README.md tool/own_doc_lint.py tool/own29_readme_friendly_toolkit_lint.hexa
  scope HARD block — README.md per-section friendly toolkit table contract. Generalized 2026-04-29 from Biology-only to multi-section spec. Each section in the registered `mandatory-sections` list must contain a friendly H2 heading + 6-column toolkit table + >=N data rows + valid `[doc](domains/<axis>/<slug>/<slug>.md)` link per row. Sections in `optional-sections` are checked when present (toolkit table found → 4-axis check applied) but absence is allowed. Sections not in either list are skipped.
  mandatory-sections biology=## 🧬 Molecular Toolkit (HEXA family)|min_rows=4|axis=biology
  optional-sections ai_ml=## 🤖 AI Toolkit (HEXA-AI family)|min_rows=3|axis=compute
  optional-sections environment=## 🌿 Environment Toolkit (HEXA-Earth family)|min_rows=3|axis=infra
  optional-sections energy=## ⚡ Energy Toolkit (HEXA-Power family)|min_rows=3|axis=infra
  optional-sections robotics=## 🤖 Robotics Toolkit (HEXA-Mech family)|min_rows=3|axis=robotics
  optional-sections physics_math=## 🔬 Physics Toolkit (HEXA-Phys family)|min_rows=3|axis=physics
  expected-header-row | Tool | One-liner | Everyday analogy | What it does | <Mainstream> contrast | Doc |
  status live
  since 2026-04-29
  why README.md Biology section accumulated dense technical table only (cycle 14-22 evolution); cycle 25 introduced friendly Molecular Toolkit (HEXA family) 6-column block at user direction. cycle 25 strengthening: generalize beyond Biology so any domain section can register a toolkit table; mandatory-list grows as sections are filled. lint enforcement covers presence + structure + doc-link resolution.
  note enforcement = lint scan on README.md only (no recursive scan). 4-axis check per registered section: H2 heading present + 6-column header (exact column-name template, allowing per-section <Mainstream> contrast variation) + >=min_rows data rows + each row's doc link resolves. own 1 English-only still applies. mandatory list growth: append entries to `mandatory-sections` as user approves each section; optional list is for pre-registered candidates that lint will check IF the section's toolkit table appears.
  verify python3 tool/own_doc_lint.py --rule 29
  cron on-commit
  on_fail block
  label own#29 readme-friendly-toolkit HARD gate (multi-section)
